Shortbread

Ingredients (Serves 2)

Dough
	•	6½ tablespoons unsalted butter (just under ½ cup)
	•	1 cup all-purpose flour
	•	⅓ cup + 1 tablespoon powdered sugar
	•	¼ teaspoon fine sea salt

⸻

Method
	1.	Heat Oven
Preheat to 320°F (160°C). Line a baking tray with parchment.
	2.	Brown Butter
Melt butter in a light-colored saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until milk solids turn hazelnut-brown and smell nutty.
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes.
	3.	Mix Base
Whisk browned butter with powdered sugar and salt until smooth and glossy.
	4.	Form Dough
Gently fold in flour just until combined. Do not overmix.
Rest dough 10 minutes.
	5.	Shape
Press dough into a 1 cm (≈1/2 in) thick disc on parchment. Lightly score portions.
	6.	Bake
Bake 25–30 minutes until edges are pale gold and the center is set (top should remain light).
	7.	Cool & Cut
Cool on tray 10 minutes, then transfer to a rack. Cut along score lines once fully set.

⸻

Optional Enhancements
	•	Dust lightly with powdered sugar after cooling
	•	Add lemon zest or vanilla to the butter-sugar mixture
	•	Use muscovado sugar (finely blitzed) for deeper bitterness
	•	Chill dough overnight for slightly crisper structure